[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     46[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe problem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The Encryption row says "DynamoDB: encryption at rest (default)." AWS default DynamoDB encryption uses AWS-owned keys, not customer-managed keys. For PHI data under HIPAA, many compliance programs require customer-managed KMS keys (CMK) on all PHI stores for audit trail visibility and key revocation capability. The S3 configuration correctly specifies SSE-KMS, creating an inconsistency in the PHI encryption posture.[K
